message.content: cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. The paper focuses on the task of Visual Question Answering (VQA) and proposes a system that uses Visual Question Generation (VQG) to produce questions, asks them to social media users, and collects their responses. This involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms and machine learning models, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.IR.
